President Muhammadu Buhari has appointed four new Permanent Secretaries into the Federal Civil Service. The Head of the Civil Service of the Federation (HOCSF), Dr Folasade Yemi-Esan made this known in a statement issued on Monday in Abuja, by Mrs Olawunmi Ogunmosunle, Director Information, office of the HOCSF. According to the statement, those appointed are Mr Sule James from Kaduna, Mr Abubakar Ismaila from Kebbi, Mrs Patricia Roberts from Rivers and Mr Shehu Shinkafi from Zamfara State. The statement also said the swearing-in and the deployment will be announced in due course, NAN reports.